    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="1601"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1601">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.62/107.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Special Agent <persName type="to">Carothers</persName>.</hi>
                    <note n="154" xml:id="d1601fn154">Communicated to the German Embassy November 9,
                        1914.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 7, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department informed that German Vice Consul at Guanajuato is proprietor of
                    Hacienda Santiago in Villanueva, Zacatecas, and that this property has been
                    seized by R. S. Garay, Jefe de Armas, who claims to be acting under orders from
                    General Villa.</p>
                <p>At request of German Embassy this capital, please bring to attention of General
                    Villa and use your best efforts to have this property restored to rightful
                    owner.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
